import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.histplot(data['values'])
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the distribution of elevation values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.boxplot(data=data, y='height')
    avg_height = data['height'].mean()
    plt.axhline(avg_height, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Height: {avg_height:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average height of the volcano?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    max_elevation = data['values'].max()
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='values', kde=True)
    plt.axvline(max_elevation, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Max Elevation: {max_elevation:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the highest elevation value in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
